-- Francesco Molinari of Italy Wins Golf’s Spanish Open by 3 Shots
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-05-06T16:03:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-06/francesco-molinari-of-italy-wins-golf-s-spanish-open-by-3-shots.html
Francesco Molinari of  Italy  scored a
final-round 65, 7-under par, to win golf’s Spanish Open by three
shots today, his first victory since 2010.  Spanish duo Alejandro Canizares and Pablo Larrazabal
finished joint second on 5-under with Denmark’s Soren Kjeldsen.  Overnight leader Simon Dyson of England slumped to a 76 and
finished down the field on 1-under par.  The winner picked up a prize of 333,330 euros ($436,000).
His last victory was the HSBC Champions in Shanghai in November
2010.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 